data.name: Roasted Garlic Tomato Toast
data.quickTastyDescription: A deliciously simple yet elegant toast topped with roasted garlic and juicy tomatoes, perfect for a light meal or snack.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the top off the garlic bulb to expose the cloves, drizzle with olive oil, and wrap it in foil.
Place the garlic in the oven and roast for about 30-40 minutes until soft and caramelized.
While the garlic is roasting, slice the sourdough bread and arrange it on a baking sheet.
Drizzle the bread with olive oil and toast it in the oven for about 8-10 minutes, until golden brown.
Meanwhile, halve the cherry tomatoes and mix them in a bowl with fresh basil, balsamic vinegar, salt, and pepper.
Once the garlic is done, squeeze the roasted cloves out into a small bowl and mash them with a fork.
Spread the roasted garlic on each slice of toasted sourdough bread, then top with the tomato mixture.
Serve immediately and enjoy your delicious roasted garlic tomato toast.
data.detailedName: Roasted Garlic Tomato Toast with Fresh Basil and Balsamic
